WINGSTROKE


“Wingstroke” (Udar krïla), written in October 1923, was published in Russkoye Ekho (The Russian Echo), an émigré periodical in Berlin, in January 1924, and now in the current collections. Although the story is set in Zermatt, it refracts the recollection of a brief vacation Nabokov had taken i